  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the majority of backdoor attack methods focus on simple learning tasks, e.g., classification (BadPrompt [21], ProAttack [321], LLMBkd [309], and BadChain [292]).",
    "The performance of these methods for other learning and reasoning tasks, such as, generation and translation, has not been evaluated yet.",
    "The performance of ProAttack is inconsistent at lower poisoning rates [321].",
    "Several backdoor attack methods, e.g., BadAgent [272], have been primarily evaluated on small-scale LLMs with 6B and 13B parameters; their effectiveness on large-scale LLMs, such as GPT-3 with 175B parameters, still remains unexplored.",
    "Data PoisoningAttack."
